  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> chicken thighs</strong> with a pinch of<strong> </strong>both<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until they're browned</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Cut a few<strong> </strong>rounds from your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> (set them aside for garnish!), then cut the <strong>remaining red</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once the chicken has browned, add a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook, covered for 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, add your<strong> wholewheat noodles</strong> to a large pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 4 min</p><p>Drain the<strong> soaked noodles</strong>, and reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring green[s]</strong>, then rip the leaves off, discard the tough stalks, and layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, remove the pan from the heat and shred the <strong>chicken</strong> apart with two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Once pulled, return the pan to a medium heat and add the<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml] </span><strong>water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the chicken is coated in a sticky sauce – this is your <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>hoisin chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced spring greens</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 1 min or until starting to wilt</p><p>Add a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook, covered, for 2 min or until completely wilted, then stir in the <strong>cooked noodles</strong>,<strong> toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> – these are your <strong>sesame noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1006.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pulled hoisin chicken</strong> over the<strong> sesame noodles</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong>,<strong> reserved chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
